All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Ant
The class represent an Ant for use by the @code{AntColonyOptimisationSolver} class.
AntColonyOptimizationSolver
Class uses the Ant colony optimisation algorithm to solve an optimised route through a TSPGraph object.
AtomicDouble
Class used to allow Ant threads to manipulate doubles in the pheromone and probabilty matrices without concurrency issues.
BruteForceSolver
Class contains logic to solve TSPGraphs containing node sets using the brute force method by finding the permutations of node orders and traversing them all to find the shortest route.
ChristofidesSolver
Used to find a route through a @code{TSPGraph} using Christofide's algorithm.
Coordinate
Used to represent coordinates.
CoordinateListExhaustionException
Thrown when the coordinate file reader has viewed all coordinate lists in the file.
CoordinateListFileReader
Class contains the functionality to load graphs from file.
CoordinateListFileWriter
Class contains functionality to handle writing graphs into file by constructing lists of coordinate objects.
CoordinateMover
CoordinateMover class is used to move a coordinate along/up/down one value depending on the method called.
DTSPGraph
Class combines the @code{TSPGraph} and @code{CoordinateMover} classes to create a dynamic travelling salesperson problem graph where the nodes move.
EdgeSuperimpositionException
Exception used to throw an error when two edges attempt to join the same nodes.
EdgeToSelfException
Exception thrown when an attempt is made to create an edge to and from the same node.
FractalDensityException
Thrown when a fractal solver was unable to create a dense enough fractal to visit all nodes on a graph.
HilbertFractalCurveAnimator
Animates a Hilbert fractal curve generated inside a @code{HilbertFractalCurveSolver} onto a java fx canvas.
HilbertFractalCurveSolver
Class constructs hilbert fractal curves and then uses the path to solve a TSPGraph route.
InvalidGraphException
Exception used to help identify when a solution is fed an invalid graph.
Main
 
Main2
 
NearestNeighbourSolver
This class takes a graph object as a parameter, and will create a TSP route using the 'Nearest Neighbour Algorithm'.
NoClosestNodeException
Thrown when no closest node can be found to a node.
NodeMissedException
Thrown when a HilbertFractalCurveSolver has constructed a curve that has missed a node during a solve.
NodeSuperimpositionException
Exception used to throw an error when two nodes attempt to occupy the same coordinate.
NonExistentNodeException
Exception used to help identify when a solution has encountered a node ID that is not in an initialized TSPNode object.
NonSquareCanvasException
Thrown when a canvas input into a @code{HilbertFractalCurveAnimator} or @code{HilbertFractalCurveSolve} is not a perfect square.
PermutationExhaustionException
Exception used to help identify when a @code{Permuter} object viewed all the permutations.
PermutationFocusException
Thrown by a @code{Permuter} object if its @code{focusIdx} attribute encounters list index errors.
Permuter<T>
This class is used to calculate and manage the permutations of a list object.
RadiusExceedingBoundaryException
Used to show when the input radius of an irregular polygon graph is higher than the possible width or height for that irregular polygon.
RepeatedFunctions
Class contains some useful functions that are repeated multiple times in the project (or have no obvious space).
SuperimpositionException
Exception thrown when an object is superimposed on another within the TSP space.
TSPEdge
Used to link two TSPNodes together.
TSPEdgeContainer
Used to manage a set of TSPEdge objects for use in TSPGraph objects.
TSPGraph
Class used to represent and collate data on a travelling salesperson problem graph.
TSPGraphAnimator
Class runs at frame rate and views the graph object input during construction and then updates the canvas object input during construction to represent what the graph looks like in that during that moment.
TSPGraphGenerator
Class contains functionality to generate TSPGraph objects of certain types or with certain properties.
TSPNode
Used to represent nodes (cities) in the TSP.
TSPNodeContainer
Used to manage sets of nodes for use in TSPGraph objects.
